LGH again ranked among best hospitals

BYLINE: By, Staff report

SECTION: BUSINESS; Pg. A15

LENGTH: 233 words


Lancaster General Hospital (LGH) was again recognized among U.S. News & World
Report's Best Hospitals for 2016-17. The hospital, which is part of University
of Pennsylvania Health System (Penn Medicine), earned a best ranking in two
specialties and was ranked fifth among Pennsylvania hospitals. Additionally, LGH
earned "high performing" rankings in five specialties.

Lancaster General Hospital ranked "best" nationally in the specialties of
gastroenterology and GI surgery, and pulmonology. LGH's "high performing"
specialties are: diabetes and endocrinology, geriatrics, nephrology, neurology
and neurosurgery, and orthopedics.

The annual U.S. News Best Hospitals rankings recognize hospitals that excel in
treating patients. The report strives to identify hospitals that provide
high-quality care for complicated illnesses and for common care. It bases the
rankings on factors including patient outcomes, nurse staffing levels and
surveys of physicians.

Other Penn Medicine hospitals earned top honors in the rankings. Together, the
combined enterprise of the Hospital of the University of Pennsylvania and Penn
Presbyterian Medical Center was ranked as the ninth best hospital in the United
States on the magazine's "Honor Roll," and was ranked first in the state of
Pennsylvania. Chester County Hospital was ranked 12th in the state.

More about the Best Hospitals rankings can be found at usnews.com.

